# HTTP & APIs

## C# → Node

| C# | Node / TS |
|----|-----------|
| `HttpClient` | native `fetch()` (Node 18+) or `axios` |
| `GetAsync(url)` | `fetch(url)` |
| `PostAsJsonAsync(url, body)` | `fetch(url, { method: 'POST', headers, body: JSON.stringify(body) })` |
| `ReadFromJsonAsync<T>()` | `(await res.json()) as T` + runtime validation |
| `HttpClientFactory` | create reusable client module or use `axios.create()` |
| `[ApiController]` + routes | Express, Fastify, Hono, or NestJS (closest to ASP.NET MVC) |

## Minimal fetch Example

```typescript
const res = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ model: 'gpt-4o', messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'Hi' }] }),
});

if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}: ${await res.text()}`);
const data = await res.json();
```

## Streaming (common in Applied AI)

- C#: `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` / `ReadAsStreamAsync`
- Node: `response.body` is a `ReadableStream`; iterate with `for await (const chunk of stream)`

## Server Side

- **Express** — most tutorials; middleware pipeline like ASP.NET middleware.
- **Fastify** — faster, schema validation built-in.
- **NestJS** — Angular-style DI; closest mental model to ASP.NET Core for C# devs.
